Background

		Mr. James M. Moroney, III, also known as Jim, has been the Chief Executive Officer of A. H. Belo Corporation since September 2013 and also serves as its President. Mr. Moroney serves as the Chief Executive Officer and Publisher of DMNmedia. Mr. Moroney has been the Chief Executive Officer and Publisher of The Dallas Morning News Inc., a subsidiary of Belo Corp. since June 2001. He served as Executive Vice President of A. H. Belo Corporation. since December 2007 until ... September 2013. He served as Executive Vice President of A. H. Belo Corporation. from July 1998 to December 1999, with responsibilities for finance, treasury and investor relations. He served as Treasurer at Newspaper Association of America. He joined Belo Corp. in November 1978. He served as President of Belo Interactive, Inc. from May 1999 to June 2001. He served as President of the Television Group from January 1997 to July 1998 and as Executive Vice President of the Television Group from January 1995 to January 1997. He serves as the Chairman of A. H. Belo Corporation. He serves as Chairman of the Board of the Newspaper Association of America. He served as the Vice Chairman of Newspaper Association of America. Mr. Moroney serves as a Director of Dallas Chamber of Commerce, The Associated Press, Inc., Cistercian Preparatory School in Dallas and the State Fair of Texas. He has been a Director of A. H. Belo Corporation since September 2013. He served as a Director of Belo Corp. since February 2008. He was named “Publisher of the Year” by Editor and Publisher magazine in 2003. In 2012, he received the Frank W. Mayborn Award from The Texas Daily Newspaper Association for Community Leadership. Mr. Moroney graduated from Stanford University in 1978 with a B.A. in American Studies. In 1983, he received his M.B.A. from the University of Texas at Austin.Read Full Background




